accessibility.text: 1. Listening Session - Lets listen to music that we love and talk about it!
2. Musical Analysis - After the listening session, we will discuss the music and try to pick it apart.
3. What is Harmony? - Main topic for this lesson.
4. Emotional Context - Section diving into how differences in harmony can affect our emotions while listening to music.
4.1. Breaking down stereotypes and biases associated with tempo.
5. Harmony Exercises - Hands-on activities centered around the topic of tempo in music.

Options (adaptable): Play with the Noise and Buttons app, Watch videos about harmony, Sing or play instruments to music, Analyze more music and either talk about, write about, or sketch about findings and emotions associated with harmony.
6. Musical Playtime - Time to mess around with musical instruments and software, create original music, or listen to music.
